# =============================================================================
#  USAGE — copy this file to  .env   (use .env, NOT .env.local)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#    cp .env.example .env        # then fill in the values below
#
#  • .env is the convention for this Python project. (.env.local is a Node/
#    Next.js idiom — nothing here uses it.) Both are gitignored, so your real
#    key is never committed: .gitignore ignores `.env` and `.env.*` but keeps
#    `.env.example`.
#  • This app reads real process environment variables and does NOT auto-load
#    .env (no python-dotenv dependency). Load it into your shell first:
#        set -a && source .env && set +a
#    …or export the var directly:
#        export DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-...
#  • Everything runs offline with ZERO keys by default; the values below are
#    only needed for the live Qwen Cloud path.
# =============================================================================

# ── Qwen Cloud (DashScope) — optional, LiveQwen transport only ─
# Offline judging and the default FakeQwen transport need NONE of these.
# Get from: https://dashscope.console.aliyun.com/apiKey
DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-your-dashscope-key-here

# ── Signing / sealing seeds — optional, deterministic dev/test only ─
# Fixed 64-hex-char seeds so the Ed25519 op-chain signature and the
# PyNaCl SealedBox key are reproducible across runs. Omit in production —
# a random seed is generated per store if unset.
# Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
# LAMPLIGHT_SIGNING_SEED_HEX=your-64-char-hex-seed-here
# LAMPLIGHT_SEAL_SEED_HEX=your-64-char-hex-seed-here

# ── Fixtures path override — optional ───────────────────────────
# Only needed if running scripts/CLI commands from outside build/.
# LAMPLIGHT_FIXTURES=/absolute/path/to/fixtures/ward_5day
